This paper discusses the security of blockchain networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed methodology involves the use of intelligent software agents and machine learning algorithms, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of algorithmic game theory, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of data and detection of anomalies, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
